Shriram Transport Falls Most in Month as Interest Margin Narrows

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-04-29T09:36:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/shriram-transport-falls-most-in-month-as-interest-margin-narrows.html
 Shriram Transport Finance Co.
dropped the most in a month after net interest margin at the
Indian truck financier narrowed.  The shares dropped as much as 3.3 percent to 772 rupees,
steepest intraday decline since March 24, and traded at 773.3
rupees, down 3.2 percent as of 3:04 p.m. in Mumbai.  Profit in the three months ended March 31 rose 30 percent
to 3.42 billion rupees, the company said in an exchange filing.
Revenue climbed 14 percent to 13.62 billion rupees. Still, net
interest margin contracted to 8.06 percent from 8.91 percent in
the quarter ended Dec. 31, said Abhishek Kothari, an analyst at
Way2Wealth Brokers Pvt. in Mumbai.  “A hit of 85 basis points in one of the highest in a
quarter in the sector,” he said.  Indian financer of trucks backed by TPG Capital, dropped to the
